<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is all pretty late-breaking and it is a l=
ittle hard to tell what is going on, but one can make some assumptions. My =
main assumption is that if you are a crypto exchange facing a =E2=80=9Csign=
ificant liquidity crunch,=E2=80=9D and you call up a bigger crypto exchange=
 to ask for help, and you sign a deal for them to buy you the same day, the=
n the price that they are paying you is, roughly speaking, zero. I mean! Pr=
obably it is not actually zero. But the basic levers here are:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you are a crypto exchange and you =
have a liquidity crunch and you cannot process withdrawals, and you=C2=A0<e=
m>don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>get a bailout, then your future equity value is b=
asically zero. If you tweet to all your customers =E2=80=9Csorry we=E2=80=
=99re out of money for a bit so no more trading and we=E2=80=99re going to =
hang on to=C2=A0<em>your=C2=A0</em>money, but things will get better,=E2=80=
=9D they will not get better.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;=
">You know that, and the buyer knows that, so if they say =E2=80=9Cwe will =
buy your exchange, make sure that all your customers are made whole, and gi=
ve you a Snickers bar in exchange for 100% of the equity,=E2=80=9D that is =
better than you=E2=80=99ll do=C2=A0<em>without=C2=A0</em>them.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You don=E2=80=99t have a ton of time to negoti=
ate, and they don=E2=80=99t have a ton of time to do due diligence. How doe=
s the buyer know that there are no huge disasters lurking on your balance s=
heet? They don=E2=80=99t, and they don=E2=80=99t have much time to find out=
, and your liquidity crunch is not an encouraging=C2=A0sign. You are having=
 a disaster now!</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Obviously if=C2=
=A0<em>lots=C2=A0</em>of buyers are competing to buy you then you can do=C2=
=A0better than a Snickers bar, if solving your liquidity crunch will fix th=
e problem and you are a profitable exchange with valuable assets. But if yo=
u are a very big exchange there are not that many buyers, and if you need a=
 deal=C2=A0<em>today=C2=A0</em>then your chances of spinning up an auction =
are low.</li>
